      • releaseVehicle

        @Deprecated
 @ScheduledApiChange(when="5.0")
void releaseVehicle(TCSObjectReference<Vehicle> ref)
                                                          throws ObjectUnknownException,
                                                                 KernelRuntimeException
        已过时。 Withdraw the vehicle's transport order and set its integration level to Vehicle.IntegrationLevel#TO_BE_IGNORED instead.
        Reset a vehicle's position, implicitly aborting any transport order it is currently processing, disabling it for transport order disposition and freeing any allocated resources.
        参数:
        ref - A reference to the vehicle.
        抛出:
        ObjectUnknownException - If the referenced vehicle does not exist.
        KernelRuntimeException - In case there is an exception executing this method.

      • withdrawByVehicle

        void withdrawByVehicle(TCSObjectReference<Vehicle> ref,
                       boolean immediateAbort)
                throws ObjectUnknownException,
                       KernelRuntimeException
        Withdraw any order that a vehicle might be processing.
        参数:
        ref - A reference to the vehicle to be modified.
        immediateAbort - If false, this method once will initiate the withdrawal, leaving the transport order assigned to the vehicle until it has finished the movements that it has already been ordered to execute. The transport order's state will change to TransportOrder.State.WITHDRAWN. If true, the dispatcher will withdraw the order from the vehicle without further waiting.
        抛出:
        ObjectUnknownException - If the referenced vehicle does not exist.
        KernelRuntimeException - In case there is an exception executing this method.

      • withdrawByVehicle

        @Deprecated
 @ScheduledApiChange(when="5.0")
void withdrawByVehicle(TCSObjectReference<Vehicle> ref,
                                                                    boolean immediateAbort,
                                                                    boolean disableVehicle)
                                                             throws ObjectUnknownException,
                                                                    KernelRuntimeException
        已过时。 Use withdrawByVehicle(org.opentcs.data.TCSObjectReference, boolean) instead.
        Withdraw any order that a vehicle might be processing, set its state to TransportOrder.State.FAILED and stop the vehicle.
        参数:
        ref - A reference to the vehicle to be modified.
        immediateAbort - If false, this method once will initiate the withdrawal, leaving the transport order assigned to the vehicle until it has finished the movements that it has already been ordered to execute. The transport order's state will change to TransportOrder.State.WITHDRAWN. If true, the dispatcher will withdraw the order from the vehicle without further waiting.
        disableVehicle - Whether to set the processing state of the vehicle currently processing the transport order to Vehicle.ProcState.UNAVAILABLE to prevent immediate redispatching of the vehicle.
        抛出:
        ObjectUnknownException - If the referenced vehicle does not exist.
        KernelRuntimeException - In case there is an exception executing this method.

      • withdrawByTransportOrder

        void withdrawByTransportOrder(TCSObjectReference<TransportOrder> ref,
                              boolean immediateAbort)
                       throws ObjectUnknownException,
                              KernelRuntimeException
        Withdraw the referenced order.
        参数:
        ref - A reference to the transport order to be withdrawn.
        immediateAbort - If false, this method once will initiate the withdrawal, leaving the transport order assigned to the vehicle until it has finished the movements that it has already been ordered to execute. The transport order's state will change to TransportOrder.State.WITHDRAWN. If true, the dispatcher will withdraw the order from the vehicle without further waiting.
        抛出:
        ObjectUnknownException - If the referenced transport order does not exist.
        KernelRuntimeException - In case there is an exception executing this method.

      • withdrawByTransportOrder

        @Deprecated
 @ScheduledApiChange(when="5.0")
void withdrawByTransportOrder(TCSObjectReference<TransportOrder> ref,
                                                                           boolean immediateAbort,
                                                                           boolean disableVehicle)
                                                                    throws ObjectUnknownException,
                                                                           KernelRuntimeException
        已过时。 Use withdrawByTransportOrder(org.opentcs.data.TCSObjectReference, boolean) instead.
        Withdraw the referenced order, set its state to TransportOrder.State.FAILED and stop the vehicle that might be processing it.
        参数:
        ref - A reference to the transport order to be withdrawn.
        immediateAbort - If false, this method once will initiate the withdrawal, leaving the transport order assigned to the vehicle until it has finished the movements that it has already been ordered to execute. The transport order's state will change to TransportOrder.State.WITHDRAWN. If true, the dispatcher will withdraw the order from the vehicle without further waiting.
        disableVehicle - Whether to set the processing state of the vehicle currently processing the transport order to Vehicle.ProcState.UNAVAILABLE to prevent immediate redispatching of the vehicle.
        抛出:
        ObjectUnknownException - If the referenced transport order does not exist.
        KernelRuntimeException - In case there is an exception executing this method.
